parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS Brakes Squeal Due to Debris/Dirt
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The squealing noise from the ABS brakes can be distracting and annoying, and if left unchecked, can lead to decreased braking performance, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Unusual squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
especially when driving on rough or dirty roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vacuum lock system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to decreased braking performance, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty applying the brakes
soft or spongy brake pedal
or unusual noises when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors and calipers can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to decreased braking performance, potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slipping of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk while accelerating, which can lead to accidents, especially when merging or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates between gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle jerks or lurches while accelerating
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations.
